LAGOS  – The Lagos State Government has restated its requirements for Planning Permits and Project Board to be present at every building construction site in the State. Dr. Idris Salako, the Commissioner for Physical Planning and Urban Development, yesterday directed the sealing of some property in Park View, Ikoyi and some areas in Mainland for violating these requirements. Salako said that it was mandatory for every construction site in Lagos State to produce the enabling Planning Permit on demand, in addition to having the project board erected among other requirements. -Advertisement- He reiterated that for a building to be certified fit for habitation upon its completion, it must have passed other requirements including Stage Supervision and Certification by the Lagos State Building Control Agency ( LASBCA), the essence of which is to ensure that the building meets certain quality standards. “All these conditions are part of measures to ensure proper construction of the building and guide against collapse”, he said.